  "text": "The model we describe is a new robust model and for an in vivo application is of reasonably high throughput. We hope the model can serve as a platform for the testing of other mechanisms and hypotheses to further understand the pathobiology of cigarette smoke-induced inflammation. This could also include the addition of other components to the protocol; such studies have already been carried out with the addition of bacteria to a 4 day smoke exposure [CITATION_1] .",
